explanation_1: The child may be a different color than black. Holding and drawing are different actions.

premise: A man on a speed motorcycle rides on a track.
hypothesis: The man stands on the bleachers.
explanation_1: A man cannot ride on a track and stand on the bleachers at the same time, they are to different tasks.

premise: A man and woman walking across a street next to a mural of a man giving a woman a golden apple.
hypothesis: A man and a woman sit in an auditorium listening to a speech.
explanation_1: A man and woman walking across a street can not sit in an auditorium.

premise: Two young men are competing in a taekwondo tournament.
hypothesis: Two men dance together
explanation_1: two men dancing together is contradictory to two men competing against each other.

premise: A man on a bicycle is pulling a cart full of sticks and branches down a road.
hypothesis: A man is pushing a truck full of sticks.
explanation_1: The man cannot be both pushing a truck and riding a bicycle to pull a cart at the same time.

premise: This person is having a fun time.
hypothesis: A lady is performing an art scene in the park with her brushes held up high she stares down the road
explanation_1: The lady cannot simultaneously be performing and having fun

premise: Three teenagers standing around a building.
hypothesis: The four teenagers are sitting down.
explanation_1: Three is not four.

premise: Three dogs walk together across a snowy field.
hypothesis: It is a warm, sunny day.
explanation_1: It could not be a warm. sunny day if it is snowy.

premise: Two guys are trying to catch a basketball; one guy has a Celtics jersey on and the other guy has a red jersey and a black hat.
hypothesis: People are fishing at the pond.
explanation_1: One cannot be trying to catch a basketball and fishing at the pond simultaneously.

premise: A guy in a huge wooden tub while people are looking over.
hypothesis: The man is alone.
explanation_1: The man isn't alone if there are people who are looking over.

premise: The woman is at marketplace buying fish from an Arabic person.
hypothesis: A woman is buying chicken from a Mexican person.
explanation_1: Fish is different from chicken and an Arabic person is different from a Mexican person.

premise: Young boy walking along the beach.
hypothesis: A boy is napping.
explanation_1: The boy is either napping or he is walking, but not both at the same time.

premise: Two women standing together observing their surroundings.
hypothesis: People standing in the street singing We Will Rock You.
explanation_1: They are either observing their surroundings or singing We Will Rock You.

premise: a young girl smiling with her head upside down
hypothesis: A young girl frowns as she kicks a ball too far.
explanation_1: If the girl is smiling with her head upside down, she would not be able to kick a ball, and wouldn't be frowning.

premise: A guy is on his bicycle.
hypothesis: The man is sailing.
explanation_1: A man doesn't go sailing on his bicycle.

premise: A large wet yellow dog retrives his toy.
hypothesis: The large cat is playing indoors.
explanation_1: A large dog is not a large cat.

premise: An Indian man and woman are asleep on public transport.
hypothesis: A man and woman are having a conversation.
explanation_1: They cannot be having a conversation while asleep.

premise: Two jugglers using flaming torches are performing for a crowd of people who are sitting on steps.
hypothesis: Nobody watches as two jugglers dance.
explanation_1: People are not performing when no one is watching.

premise: A girl is jumping on a trampoline with her arms in the air, while a boy in a blue shirt is bouncing on his stomach.
hypothesis: A girl swims in a pool with her brother.
explanation_1: the kids are jumping and bouncing on the trampoline not swimming

premise: A man in a mustard yellow shirt, brown pants and gray hat is looking at a cellphone while sitting next to a building.
hypothesis: The man is watching cars drive by.
explanation_1: Person that is looking at a cellphone can not be watching cars drive by at the same time.

premise: Two women having a meal, one of which is laughing.
hypothesis: Two men having a meal, one of which is laughing.
explanation_1: The two people can't be both genders, it's either men or women.

premise: Boy with floaties with his feet in the sand on the beach.
hypothesis: The boy is in a car.
explanation_1: The boy is either on the beach, or in a car.

premise: The woman tries to hide from work under a black sweatshirt, but her red corduroy pants give her away.
hypothesis: A woman is strolling down the street
explanation_1: Strolling down a street and hiding under a sweatshirt can't happen simultaneously. Physically and location-ally distinct.

premise: Two rugby teams playing in a field with a ball.
hypothesis: One rugby team is playing
explanation_1: two is contradictory to one

premise: A man in an orange snowsuit is on a dogsled in the snow.
hypothesis: A man without orange suit was sent out of snow.
explanation_1: Without orange suit is opposite of in an orange suit.

premise: A man in a red robe and sandals is walking past a small food stand.
hypothesis: The man is barefoot.
explanation_1: Someone who is wearing sandals cannot be considered barefoot.

premise: A little girl in a pink outfit pushing a little boy in a green outfit in a stroller.
hypothesis: A little girl walks her dog in the park.
explanation_1: Walking a dog is a different activity than pushing a little boy in a stroller.

premise: A man wearing sunglasses and long hair is playing a brass instrument.
hypothesis: Man sleeping in sofa after hard days work
explanation_1: The man cannot be sleeping while playing an instrument.

premise: a dog jumps into the water.
hypothesis: A lizard jumps into the water.
explanation_1: A dog is not a lizard.

premise: Three women are looking into a camera.
hypothesis: The women have their eyes closed.
explanation_1: One cannot be looking into a camera and have their eyes closed simultaneously.

premise: The blond woman is crouching in a field of pink tulips, near a grassy field and trees.
hypothesis: There is a women standing outdoors
explanation_1: Standing and crouching are different.

premise: a Guy driving the tractor with some people around him
hypothesis: A guy is jumping a tractor off of a wooden ramp in the latest Summer Olympics sport, "Tractor Jumping."
explanation_1: The guy cannot be driving the tractor and jumping off the tractor simultaneously.

premise: A young boy is sitting in a blue chair.
hypothesis: A boy standing on top of a table.
explanation_1: sitting and standing are different actions table and chair are different objects

premise: Group of people near a water fountain and a city skyline.
hypothesis: A crowd gathered inside a building.
explanation_1: The crowd would not be near a water fountain and a city skyline if they were inside a building.

premise: four people in a snow covered field with hacksaws.
hypothesis: The four people are going for a walk.
explanation_1: If they are in a field with hacksaws they are probably using them for work and not just going for a walk.

premise: A pep band in red and white uniform is playing while seated in a stadium.
hypothesis: A band stands in a field to play.
explanation_1: The band can't stand in a field to play if they are playing while seated.

premise: A man in a green jumpsuit rides an orange dirt bike around.
hypothesis: A girl is playing board games.
explanation_1: A man isn't a girl.

premise: a woman is sitting on a bench with a latte in her lap and a white dog on a blue leash to her side.
hypothesis: A woman walking her dog while holding a coffee.
explanation_1: If she is sitting, she is not walking.

premise: A man walking on a dirt road.
hypothesis: The man is sitting in the grass.
explanation_1: if the man is walking on a dirt road than he cannot be sitting in grass.

premise: Group of people, from behind, seated in a line of desks by windows in library.
hypothesis: Three men at a diner.
explanation_1: Group can't be in a library and at a diner.

premise: The man stands in a body of water near a waterfall.
hypothesis: The man is running on the beach.
explanation_1: Man is either standing near a waterfall or running on a beach

premise: The girl in a pink shirt jumps high over the grass.
hypothesis: A boy lies down.
explanation_1: One cannot be both a boy and a girl at the same time.

premise: The man in the black hat is sitting on the floor beside the green door.
hypothesis: A man is standing by the window.
explanation_1: Person who is sitting down can not be standing at the same time.

premise: On a red and orange stripe chair, a woman sits with her hand to her lips.
hypothesis: A woman sitting on her bed combing her hair.
explanation_1: If a woman sits with her hand to her lips she is not combing her hair.

premise: A young kid at the beach.
hypothesis: The beach is completely empty.
explanation_1: If there is a young kid at the beach, it is impossible that the beach is completely empty.

premise: Two men are playing music on a bench.
hypothesis: Two men share a sandwich.
explanation_1: Two men are either playing music, or are sharing a sandwich.

premise: Three people with their backs turned toward the camera that are dressed in what appears to be Viking and Hawaiian costumes with a crowd and towers in the background.
hypothesis: Three people posing for the camera.
explanation_1: Backs turned toward the camera is not the same as posing for the camera
